{"key":"post-10277161","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10277161</id>\n<content>The basic recipe of 2,1,1 in CUPS will fill five 1/2 pint wide mouth jars to the appropriate place to stop filling, which is the bottom of the threads.&amp;nbsp; The rest of the space in the jar is for the dry verm.&amp;nbsp; If you're using tyvek, you can add a bit more, but you still shouldn't fill the jar up.&amp;nbsp; You don't want brf jars to be 'dense'.&amp;nbsp; They work far better when loose and airy.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>10276879</prev>\n<first>10275416</first>\n<last>10277161</last>\n<when>1241358999</when>\n<utime>05/03/09 04:56 PM</utime>\n</post>"}